{
  "text": "During extraction using affinity chromatography, the glutathione S-transferase (GST)-LuxR fusion protein and chaperonin GroEL coelute [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, both GroEL and cochaperonin GroES were previously shown to enhance the accumulation of the soluble LuxR-like protein TraR, a quorum-sensing transcription factor from Agrobacterium tumefaciens (3).",
